        <div>
            <pb facs="#TL-0609.jpg" n="part4_p135.jpg" xml:id="img_0135" corresp="https://id.acdh.oeaw.ac.at/tillich-lectures/part4_p135.jpg"/>
            
            <p facs="#facs_135_tr_2">
               <lb facs="#facs_135_tr_2_tl_1" n="N001"/>[604]
               <lb facs="#facs_135_tr_2_tl_2" n="N002"/>whole lecture[s] summed up in a few words. We have discussed, in ALL realms the conflict
               <lb facs="#facs_135_tr_2_tl_3" n="N003"/>between <rs type="keyword" ref="#Heteronomy">heteronomy</rs> and <rs type="keyword" ref="#Autonomy">autonomy,</rs> the danger of a disintegrating autonomy, and of a tyrannical
               <lb facs="#facs_135_tr_2_tl_4" n="N004"/>heteronomy. We must open ourselves for the coming of a new <rs type="keyword" ref="#Theonomy">theonomy</rs> by realizing that
               <lb facs="#facs_135_tr_2_tl_5" n="N005"/>we cannot escape it anyhow, that the depth-dimension is IN us, and either we are aware of it
               <lb facs="#facs_135_tr_2_tl_6" n="N006"/>and express it, or it will destroy us AGAINST our will! And I think this insight makes
               <lb facs="#facs_135_tr_2_tl_7" n="N007"/>EVEN the period of EMPTINESS, and of <rs type="keyword" ref="#Anxiety">anxiety</rs>, or <hi style="font-style: italic;">Wasteland</hi>, or <hi style="font-style: italic;">No Exit</hi>, a period of
               <lb facs="#facs_135_tr_2_tl_9" n="N008"/>highest possibilities, of openness to that which ULTIMATELY counts:
               <lb facs="#facs_135_tr_2_tl_10" n="N009"/>OUR <ultimate_concern>ULTIMATE CONCERN</ultimate_concern>!
               <lb facs="#facs_135_tr_2_tl_11" n="N010"/>End of Lectures
            </p>
         
        </div>
